WEBVTT

1
00:01:10,280 --> 00:01:13,240
We really need to get first place in that Beat Contest

2
00:01:13,240 --> 00:01:15,720
We’ll win it for sure, bro, you’re just anxious.

3
00:01:15,720 --> 00:01:20,320
I don't even have any money left. My drumstick is also completely spoiled.
- There, there.

4
00:01:20,320 --> 00:01:22,480
We have Pete. He's our rich guy.

5
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:24,040
We’ll get you a new one, don’t worry.

6
00:01:24,040 --> 00:01:24,840
You swear?

7
00:01:24,840 --> 00:01:26,320
Of course.
- Yes!

8
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:27,360
Bro...

9
00:01:27,800 --> 00:01:29,880
Ah! Not you too!

10
00:01:29,880 --> 00:01:31,600
So cunning, I’ll will remember this.
-Let’s move, guys.

11
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:35,200
There’s something stuck on your hair. I’ll buy a guitar pick for you.

12
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:35,760
No.

13
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:36,280
Okay?

14
00:01:36,280 --> 00:01:37,440
No. You’ll get me an ugly pick.

15
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:39,160
No, I know a nice one, Dave.

16
00:01:39,160 --> 00:01:40,280
I don’t care.

17
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:03,600
Whose guitar did you bring home this time?

18
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:07,640
You should concentrate on your studies.

19
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:08,800
Ah, don’t worry, mom.

20
00:02:09,640 --> 00:02:11,480
You’re neglecting your studies.

21
00:02:11,480 --> 00:02:12,800
I’m definitely gonna pass the exam.

22
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:14,880
All you think about is music.

23
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:15,960
Is that chicken?

24
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:20,080
Listen to what I’m saying. How will you manage to find a job?

25
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:22,360
Look, mom. I know, I know.

26
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:24,040
How will you have the confidence to find a wife?

27
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:26,000
Ah! I’m going to study.

28
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:53,360
Damn, it’s my restricted day for driving.

29
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:03,840
How much is it till PUC?

30
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:05,680
It’s Rs.600 till the main gate.

31
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:06,880
Aish!

32
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:13,560
Get out. Don’t ever let me see you again. I can find plenty of other women.

33
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:15,400
Uh, can you go for Rs.500?

34
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:16,360
Fine, I’ll do it.

35
00:03:16,360 --> 00:03:17,240
Thank you so much.

36
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:18,880
Sir, can I get a ride?

37
00:03:18,920 --> 00:03:19,880
Where are you headed?

38
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:24,640
E, oh, you can use this. I can just hail another one.

39
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:27,000
Sir, how much is it for Khatla?

40
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:27,840
That’ll be Rs.300.

41
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:31,600
Can you drop me for Rs.150?

42
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:36,080
Young lady, that won’t be possible, you’ll have to wait for another taxi.

43
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:43,640
Here, I’ll pay for you.

44
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:47,600
Thank you so much. I’ll pay you back. Sir, Khatla.

45
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:15,560
What?

46
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:18,240
Are you on your way?

47
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:20,760
I’m studying, you should try it sometimes.

48
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:25,840
Look, we’re all waiting for you to start the jam. See? Get here fast.

49
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:27,720
I’m going to study.

50
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:34,000
The exam is still far away and the Beat Contest is just a few days away.

51
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:36,200
You’re the one to kept on stressing that it’s important.

52
00:04:36,280 --> 00:04:39,040
Get here fast. Guess we’ll see which is more important to you. Come. I’m hanging up.

53
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:17,000
Hello

54
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:21,560
Hi... oh, it’s you? Come, have a seat.

55
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:24,840
How are you?

56
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:26,720
Yes, I’m good.

57
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:28,000
I’m Zodina.

58
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:33,000
Oh, by the way, here, from the other day....

59
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:34,960
There’s no need to-

60
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,920
No... don’t say no...
- I’m serious, you don’t have to pay me back.

61
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,520
No, I feel bad... It’s such a huge amount.

62
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:41,360
Can you please take it so that I can feel better?

63
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:43,760
Oye, oye, oye. What are you gonna order?

64
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:47,400
Whatever you guys like. Uh, Dave, this is my friend…

65
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:48,480
Betsie

66
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:49,800
Betsie? Okay. I’m Dave.

67
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:52,400
Oh, did you write this? May I read it? You allow it, right?

68
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:53,680
You allow it, right?
- Go ahead...

69
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:56,320
Wow, You write songs?

70
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:58,040
Yeah, I occasionally write.

71
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:01,040
Mm! Do you make music as well?

72
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:03,360
I... kind of make it... I guess...

73
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:10,200
You know, we have a band, and if its okay with you, can you send Zodina your demo? Please?

74
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:11,360
Okay, I’ll send it to him.

75
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,720
Yes, you’re so nice.

76
00:07:12,840 --> 00:07:15,400
Uh, Excuse me, would you like to place your order?

77
00:07:15,640 --> 00:07:18,360
Wait, it’s the other table.
Send it to him, okay? I trust you.

78
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:24,120
He must have thought that we’ve known each other. I’m so sorry.
- That’s okay.

79
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:24,920
That’s okay.

80
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:30,680
Umm, while we’re at it, let’s exchange phone numbers and I’ll call you later?

81
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:31,400
Umm.

82
00:07:39,640 --> 00:07:43,960
Yes! Thank you. I’ll get going then. Buh-bye.

83
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:44,880
Buh- bye.

84
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:05,480
You came home so late, I’ve been looking forward to eating the food you have prepared.

85
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,920
I made myself free since you’re back home anyway.

86
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:09,920
Do you want to have dinner now?

87
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:12,240
No, not now. I’ll have it later.

88
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:14,520
Big sis.

89
00:08:14,960 --> 00:08:15,560
Hmm?

90
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:18,760
Boys from our locality keep on pestering me after they know about your separation.

91
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:24,440
They’d say something stupid like “When can we start courting your sister because I want to introduce her to my friend who is divorced.”

92
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:30,280
Or something like, “If I’m unmarried, or if I was still single, I wouldn’t mind courting her.”

93
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:35,440
It’s so stupid and so annoying. Men who talk excessively are not reliable sources of advice.

94
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:39,240
Ah! I don’t care so let them say whatever they want.

95
00:08:40,680 --> 00:08:43,480
These men talk endlessly even on social media.

96
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:47,200
They are often the most opinionated, even on topics related to women.
- Hello?

97
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:49,200
And the same applies to issues related to men too.

98
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:52,040
Oh, really? I’ll be so grateful if it is possible. I’m so glad.

99
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:53,000
All right.

100
00:08:57,640 --> 00:08:59,960
Oh my! You’re so crazy!

101
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:00,960
Who was it?

102
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:07,440
That was Kimi. The thing is… uh… I was thinking of staying over at Kimi’s house for the week.

103
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:09,520
Hmph!

104
00:09:33,920 --> 00:09:35,680
Ahoy! Let’s start.

105
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:36,360
Let’s start.

106
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:44,000
We have just one week left to practice for the beat contest so let’s give it our all.

107
00:09:55,920 --> 00:09:56,400
Beth,

108
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:56,960
Mm?

109
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:59,640
I have to leave early since our storekeeper is sick.

110
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:01,400
Is that so?
-  You can make whatever you want.

111
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:02,920
Ah, don’t worry about me, I’ll be all right.

112
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:06,560
By the way, bring home a smoked pork, let’s have it for dinner.

113
00:10:06,560 --> 00:10:08,720
Okay… I’ll be leaving now. Buh- bye.

114
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:09,480
Buh-bye.

115
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:18,480
Beth, I left my key on my dressing table, can you throw it from the window?

116
00:10:19,680 --> 00:10:22,040
Zoa, where are you going? You’ve got quite a handful.

117
00:10:22,360 --> 00:10:23,600
I’m heading for my class.

118
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:25,480
Oh? With the guitar?

119
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:26,840
Yeah, we’re planning to jam right after the classes.
- Kim!

120
00:10:29,680 --> 00:10:30,480
What are you doing here?

121
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:33,680
I’m staying over at Kimi’s house for a while. What about you?

122
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:35,680
This is my house.

123
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:38,600
Oh, you guys know each other?

124
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:40,920
Yeah, we do. I’ll come over some day, okay?
- Mm.

125
00:10:41,040 --> 00:10:42,040
Yes, buh- bye.

126
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:04,800
Were you feeling lonely today?

127
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:09,440
Not at all. I enjoy having some time to myself so I’m pretty okay.

128
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:11,120
I’m worried about you.

129
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:16,160
I’m scared you’ll make bad decisions because of your broken heart.

130
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:20,720
It’s just so hard to wrap my head around it.

131
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:31,920
How I have to deal with it, my family... ah… my mind is blank for now.

132
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:38,240
You need to forget your past and look towards the future.

133
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:42,280
As time passes, you'll gradually heal and move on from this.

134
00:11:42,520 --> 00:11:47,640
I guess I’ve become something I’ve never even dreamt for myself… a divorcee.

135
00:11:48,760 --> 00:11:51,200
I don’t know how to explain it, it’s so weird.

136
00:11:52,040 --> 00:11:55,360
Being a divorcee doesn’t have to shape how you live.

137
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:58,160
Be the Betsie that you’ve always been.

138
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:10,320
Be the Betsie that your family, your friends and everyone else loves. Don’t bother yourself with the rest.

139
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:21,920
I know I don’t understand the amount of pain you’re going through but I understand that you’re hurting.

140
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,320
It’ll get better, right?

141
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:27,360
It will.

142
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:30,080
Mhm.

143
00:12:31,680 --> 00:12:35,560
Shall we go to bed? I’m super sleepy. But I’ll sleep beside you, okay?

144
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:40,360
Oh, by the way, my order from Online Mizoram will arrive tomorrow. Receive that for me, okay?

145
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:40,960
Mhm.

146
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:52,080
Bro, can you tell me Rinkimi’s address?

147
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:55,080
It’s this building here but I think she has left for her shop.

148
00:12:55,280 --> 00:12:56,840
Her order has arrived.

149
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:58,960
I’ll just receive it on her behalf?

150
00:12:59,040 --> 00:12:59,960
That’ll be great.

151
00:13:17,280 --> 00:13:18,520
Here, Kimi’s package.

152
00:13:18,520 --> 00:13:20,520
Oh, thank you. I’ll give it to her.

153
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,960
By the way, I made the demo.

154
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:27,000
Is that so? Then… what’s your plan for tomorrow?

155
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:29,480
Umm… I don’t know… why?

156
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:32,760
We’re going to perform at the Beat Contest. Mind coming to watch?

157
00:13:34,680 --> 00:13:36,960
I’ll let you know tomorrow?

158
00:13:37,920 --> 00:13:38,640
Okay, bye.

159
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:38,320
Hi! You guys were amazing.

160
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:39,520
I’m glad you could make it.

161
00:15:41,760 --> 00:15:44,520
Uh, sorry for disturbing you all. You’re the Hangout Boys, right?

162
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:45,040
Yes. That’s us.

163
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:52,680
E… You are such great singers and your performance was amazing. Let me shake hands you.

164
00:15:53,400 --> 00:16:02,280
Um… I’m John. This is my business card with my details and my phone number. Contact me and we’ll find a way to work together.

165
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:04,200
Okay. Thank you so much.
- Have a great day.

166
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:07,080
Where? Let me have a look.

167
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:10,280
Oh, my! This is MN Records.

168
00:16:10,280 --> 00:16:12,520
Dave, have you heard of them?
- Its among the biggest record labels.

169
00:16:12,520 --> 00:16:14,080
I think that guy is the owner.

170
00:16:14,920 --> 00:16:15,680
I know.

171
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:16,880
Shall we go?

172
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:17,960
Let’s go. Come.

173
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:24,600
See? I told you, you guys did well. He knows how good you all are so he approached you.

174
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:26,240
It’s only because you came and watched us.

175
00:16:44,720 --> 00:16:47,040
Are you going to stay for a while at Kimi’s place?

176
00:16:47,120 --> 00:16:49,280
I was planning on going home this evening.

177
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:52,920
Then… let’s go to the café tomorrow?

178
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:57,040
I might not be available tomorrow; I plan to stay home and keep my sister company.

179
00:16:58,120 --> 00:16:59,440
Okay. Bye-bye.
- Buh-bye.

180
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:02,360
Zodin, we’ll talk later about the café.

181
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:16,880
Mm! We may not be the winners but 2nd place isn’t that bad, right, MK?

182
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:19,040
Mmm. And the contract?

183
00:17:19,600 --> 00:17:23,160
The contract, yeah, we might have a chance to have a professional contract.

184
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:25,400
Good, good. That’s good.

185
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:29,200
But, see, if we sign the contract, we’ll have to really-

186
00:17:29,320 --> 00:17:33,400
Hey, Pete, now’s not the time for that.
Come, it’s the time to enjoy.

187
00:17:33,440 --> 00:17:35,200
Let’s enjoy it. Let’s enjoy it. Let’s go!

188
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:23,640
Bro, let me tell you, I love her a lot. I really love her.

189
00:18:25,240 --> 00:18:31,840
And she called me last night. I didn’t answer but I really wanted to.

190
00:18:33,840 --> 00:18:38,480
Tell me, what’s going on between you and Betsie?

191
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:43,880
We can tell that you actually like her from the way you act.

192
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:46,240
That’s absurd! We’re just starting to know each other.

193
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:49,040
I’m serious. Don’t try to hide it.

194
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:52,000
It’s quite obvious from your actions, Zodin.

195
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:54,280
Huh!

196
00:18:54,880 --> 00:18:57,480
When you had a crush, who was the first one to notice it?

197
00:18:58,120 --> 00:18:58,920
It was me.

198
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:06,760
Even when you had a crush on a girl in class 10, who was the first one to know it? Huh?

199
00:19:08,240 --> 00:19:15,120
I read you like a book, bro. I’m serious, I know you so well and I know you like her.

200
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:17,960
You’re so a annoying. Anyway, what do you think of her?

201
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:20,120
Married women are not my type.

202
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:23,600
If you like her, you have my full support.

203
00:19:24,520 --> 00:19:26,200
I think I’m starting to really like Betsie.

204
00:19:26,680 --> 00:19:30,920
We met by coincidence and what if I’m destined to be with her?

205
00:19:31,200 --> 00:19:36,560
I know so many people who broke up who thought they were destined to be together.

206
00:19:38,160 --> 00:19:41,800
If the two of you truly like each other, go pay the bride price now.

207
00:19:42,240 --> 00:19:43,600
You are so drunk.

208
00:19:43,600 --> 00:19:49,960
Ah… bro. I speak nothing but the truth. My only problem is that I’m so smart.

209
00:19:51,080 --> 00:19:52,200
You just don’t understand.

210
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:53,120
Such nonsense.

211
00:19:53,880 --> 00:20:07,120
On a serious note, Zodin, you have to think about yourself. Once you lift yourself higher, girls will come. Definitely.

212
00:20:08,080 --> 00:20:09,880
You are so wasted.

213
00:20:10,720 --> 00:20:13,840
Zodin, look up at the sky.

214
00:20:15,960 --> 00:20:17,680
It has no limit.

215
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:25,000
The stars will know of our story.

216
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:34,960
I’m telling you
The Sky is Ours.

217
00:20:44,880 --> 00:20:46,760
Oh, you were able to make it.

218
00:20:47,040 --> 00:20:49,920
Come sit, come sit. Feel free to pull the chairs.

219
00:20:50,720 --> 00:20:53,200
Oh, you guys seem to run a little late.

220
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:55,560
We stayed up late last night. We’re so sorry.
- I understand.

221
00:20:55,560 --> 00:21:00,160
All right, anyway, we have drafted your contract,

222
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:08,840
Read it carefully, everything that you need to know, like how much you’re getting paid and what we expect from you,

223
00:21:09,080 --> 00:21:13,520
Everything has been clearly stated, read it thoroughly and if you can sign it…

224
00:21:14,360 --> 00:21:15,080
We’ll sign it.

225
00:21:15,080 --> 00:21:17,560
You’re ready to sign? This is great news.

226
00:21:18,360 --> 00:21:20,960
Just sign under each of your names.

227
00:21:20,960 --> 00:21:23,320
Are you all excited?
All: Yes, we are.

228
00:21:23,320 --> 00:21:26,040
You will become a global sensation.

229
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:33,440
Finally, I welcome you all to MN Records. Let’s shake hands.

230
00:21:36,120 --> 00:21:38,000
Do you want to see your new studio?

231
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:38,600
Yeah.
- Yes,

232
00:21:38,600 --> 00:21:40,480
You want to see it now? Follow me.

233
00:21:44,040 --> 00:21:45,440
This is it.

234
00:21:45,880 --> 00:21:46,840
Come in, come in.

235
00:21:46,840 --> 00:21:48,400
This is so amazing!

236
00:21:50,280 --> 00:21:52,200
Woah!

237
00:21:52,400 --> 00:21:53,640
How is it? Is it to your liking?

238
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:54,920
Sir, this is more than what we have imagined.

239
00:21:54,920 --> 00:21:56,600
Oh, really? Glad to hear that.

240
00:21:57,880 --> 00:22:00,080
So, for your first task… hehe

241
