Lay down here… and keep your legs straight.
- I’m okay.

500
00:43:29,640 --> 00:43:31,160
I’ll be okay…

501
00:43:32,600 --> 00:43:34,040
- 00:45:33:16
I’ll get more water, okay?

502
00:43:34,240 --> 00:43:35,000
Mm.

503
00:43:35,160 --> 00:43:36,760
I’ll bring a paracetamol too.

504
00:43:56,040 --> 00:43:57,400
The call is not getting through?

505
00:43:58,080 --> 00:43:59,560
He isn’t picking up…

506
00:43:59,560 --> 00:44:00,720
It’s so annoying.

507
00:44:03,440 --> 00:44:05,640
Oh, sir, how are you?

508
00:44:05,640 --> 00:44:07,400
How have you been?
- I’m John.

509
00:44:07,400 --> 00:44:10,920
You guys are good? Able to reach home safe? Where’s Dave?

510
00:44:11,080 --> 00:44:12,560
Our calls can’t get through.

511
00:44:12,560 --> 00:44:13,720
Oh… okay…

512
00:44:13,960 --> 00:44:18,720
E… yeah, since I couldn’t join you… you guys faced any trouble?

513
00:44:18,720 --> 00:44:19,920
No trouble at all, sir. We’re really grateful.

514
00:44:19,920 --> 00:44:21,200
Did you all enjoy the trip?

515
00:44:23,040 --> 00:44:27,120
Just that Pete can’t different between a girl and a boy, apart from that, no trouble at all.

516
00:44:27,400 --> 00:44:28,680
Oh... that’s horrible.

517
00:44:28,680 --> 00:44:29,840
Zodina was just kidding.

518
00:44:29,840 --> 00:44:36,840
Yeah, you have to be careful in Thailand…They all look the same so unless you touch it, you can’t differentiate them anymore.

519
00:44:37,000 --> 00:44:45,040
So, Zodin, did Betsie enjoy the trip? We guys would have stuck together like glue.

520
00:44:45,480 --> 00:44:49,080
They say that falling for a married woman hits differently.

521
00:44:49,200 --> 00:44:58,840
On a serious note, the reason I urgently asked you guys here is because we’re nearing the end of the year and there are going to be quite a lot of events.

522
00:44:58,840 --> 00:45:08,360
You will be fairly busy and our biggest challenge and our main goal will be winning the Thazual Award

523
00:45:08,360 --> 00:45:16,840
Even if you don’t have much free time, just remember that all this hard work will pay off in the end, it won’t go in vain.

524
00:45:17,200 --> 00:45:20,360
And if I’m not mistaken, day after tomo-

525
00:45:20,360 --> 00:45:22,160
Hello!

526
00:45:23,880 --> 00:45:30,040
E... you... come over here.

527
00:45:31,920 --> 00:45:34,120
Mm. here, let’s shake hands as well.

528
00:45:35,440 --> 00:45:40,360
Hold on. E… you still reek of Bangkok.

529
00:45:40,880 --> 00:45:48,120
Huh… just go and sit down. Ask your friends all the important things I said. Tell Dave what we have discussed.

530
00:45:48,120 --> 00:45:48,880
Yes.

531
00:45:49,480 --> 00:45:53,800
As I was saying, day after tomorrow, which is on the 9th, you will have a gig

532
00:45:53,800 --> 00:45:59,680
You might be tired to practice immediately but you’ll have to start from tomorrow.

533
00:45:59,880 --> 00:46:02,000
Uh, Dave will also drink lots of water
- Yes!

534
00:46:02,000 --> 00:46:03,600
You’ll be up for it tomorrow, right?
- I will!

535
00:46:03,600 --> 00:46:04,920
Ah, that’s good.

536
00:46:09,520 --> 00:46:11,080
They flew home yesterday.

537
00:46:11,080 --> 00:46:11,960
Oh, really?

538
00:46:11,960 --> 00:46:12,040
Mm. Go look at Mka’s story.

539
00:46:12,040 --> 00:46:15,120
Gosh, I like Pete so much, and he’s so cool!

540
00:46:17,000 --> 00:46:18,520
Zodina is much better.

541
00:46:18,720 --> 00:46:20,960
Mka is so adorable.

542
00:46:21,160 --> 00:46:26,040
Who should I like? Pete or Dave? But I heard Dave is such a womanizer.

543
00:46:26,040 --> 00:46:27,200
See? Rin, you have a chance.

544
00:46:27,200 --> 00:46:30,360
Go away! I heard people say that Zodina’s girlfriend has been married before.

545
00:46:30,360 --> 00:46:31,440
Is that true?

546
00:46:31,600 --> 00:46:34,280
It’s such a pity, Zodina is still so young.

547
00:46:34,400 --> 00:46:37,320
She went to Thailand with them, like, what did she even do?

548
00:46:37,600 --> 00:46:38,560
Exactly.

549
00:46:39,080 --> 00:46:41,520
Get divorced, he might like you back.

550
00:46:41,640 --> 00:46:43,520
Should I? He might like me cuz of it.

551
00:46:43,560 --> 00:46:45,080
He obviously will like you!

552
00:46:48,120 --> 00:46:50,520
Bro, did Betsie come today?

553
00:46:50,840 --> 00:46:52,240
Uh, the girl with the short hair?

554
00:46:52,680 --> 00:46:54,400
She came but she left really early.

555
00:46:55,040 --> 00:46:57,680
Zodin, can my friend take a photo with you?

556
00:46:57,680 --> 00:46:59,800
I’m so sorry but I am in a bit of a hurry.

557
00:47:00,040 --> 00:47:01,000
Oh, okay.

558
00:47:05,480 --> 00:47:06,440
Come in.

559
00:47:06,440 --> 00:47:07,360
Is anyone home?

560
00:47:07,360 --> 00:47:09,600
Oh, Zodin, where’s my sister?

561
00:47:09,600 --> 00:47:10,400
She’s not at home?

562
00:47:10,520 --> 00:47:12,960
No, she left in the morning. I thought you went out together.

563
00:47:12,960 --> 00:47:13,960
No… didn’t go out together.

564
00:47:13,960 --> 00:47:16,040
Have a seat. I’ll go make tea.

565
00:47:16,040 --> 00:47:17,520
Okay. Let’s have tea.

566
00:47:23,200 --> 00:47:24,480
Did you enjoy the trip?

567
00:47:24,480 --> 00:47:25,560
It was good.

568
00:47:26,160 --> 00:47:27,160
What did you get me?

569
00:47:27,160 --> 00:47:28,720
Nothing, brought back your sister.

570
00:47:29,440 --> 00:47:30,800
I really wanted to come as well.

571
00:47:31,320 --> 00:47:32,720
Did you talk to Pete for me?

572
00:47:32,840 --> 00:47:38,720
Pete? He doesn’t care about these things. You have to act first.

573
00:47:38,720 --> 00:47:40,280
I’m too shy to talk to him!

574
00:47:40,280 --> 00:47:41,520
You shouldn’t be shy!

575
00:47:41,520 --> 00:47:43,720
I thought you’d say something to him at least.

576
00:47:43,920 --> 00:47:45,360
I’ll tell him if I don’t forget it.
- Mmm.

577
00:47:46,080 --> 00:47:47,560
Mm. I’ll go take care of the laundry.

578
00:48:00,360 --> 00:48:01,200
Bah!

579
00:48:01,440 --> 00:48:03,000
Oi! You scared me!

580
00:48:03,000 --> 00:48:03,920
Hello

581
00:48:04,000 --> 00:48:04,520
Hi!

582
00:48:04,520 --> 00:48:05,600
Where did you go today?

583
00:48:05,600 --> 00:48:06,560
To the café.

584
00:48:06,960 --> 00:48:09,120
I came to the café but you weren’t there.

585
00:48:09,640 --> 00:48:12,120
I didn’t feel good so I went home early.

586
00:48:12,360 --> 00:48:14,640
If that’s the case then you should’ve told me…

587
00:48:15,040 --> 00:48:16,840
You didn’t even pick up the call.

588
00:48:20,600 --> 00:48:21,720
You feel better now?

589
00:48:21,960 --> 00:48:23,200
Yeah, much better.

590
00:48:23,960 --> 00:48:26,840
Then… have dinner at my place?

591
00:48:27,880 --> 00:48:31,160
Mom’s away, travelling and… I’ll be the chef for the night.

592
00:48:32,840 --> 00:48:35,560
I’m scared to taste your cooking

593
00:48:36,360 --> 00:48:37,960
Fine, don’t come and eat.

594
00:48:40,320 --> 00:48:43,560
Hey, I was kidding! Where are you even going?

595
00:49:07,480 --> 00:49:08,840
What are you doing here, Mk?

596
00:49:08,960 --> 00:49:13,720
My family told me to buy some groceries. What about you?

597
00:49:14,160 --> 00:49:15,600
I’m having Betsie over for dinner

598
00:49:15,600 --> 00:49:17,040
That’s gonna be fun.

599
00:49:17,040 --> 00:49:18,120
Don’t forget the jam on Friday.

600
00:49:18,120 --> 00:49:18,840
Yeah, yeah.

601
00:49:22,640 --> 00:49:26,280
Thank you. Mk, take your salary on your way out.

602
00:49:49,200 --> 00:49:50,560
Hi
- Hello

603
00:49:50,560 --> 00:49:51,560
Come on in.

604
00:49:51,720 --> 00:49:53,160
You look amazing.

605
00:49:53,160 --> 00:49:54,960
That’s so nice of you to say.

606
00:49:55,120 --> 00:49:55,920
Come.

607
00:49:59,760 --> 00:50:02,920
Let me get the chair for you.

608
00:50:04,080 --> 00:50:05,240
Are you hungry?

609
00:50:05,520 --> 00:50:07,680
Not much, I ate something earlier.

610
00:50:08,200 --> 00:50:09,520
Very well then.

611
00:50:12,480 --> 00:50:14,480
I was kidding!

612
00:50:16,040 --> 00:50:17,440
So what are you making?

613
00:50:17,720 --> 00:50:19,280
You’ll know it once I finish making it.

614
00:50:20,600 --> 00:50:22,360
Are you actually pissed off?

615
00:50:22,480 --> 00:50:23,400
No I’m not.

616
00:50:23,560 --> 00:50:24,520
You are!

617
00:50:24,520 --> 00:50:25,960
You’re so irritating!

618
00:50:45,480 --> 00:50:46,840
Tom or Jerry?

619
00:50:46,840 --> 00:50:48,120
Jerry.

620
00:50:48,400 --> 00:50:49,520
I prefer Tom

621
00:50:49,520 --> 00:50:51,840
Hmph! Just because I don’t choose him.

622
00:50:51,840 --> 00:50:57,920
Jerry always disturbs Tom while he is minding his own business, and Jerry always wins in the end.

623
00:50:57,920 --> 00:50:59,560
Don’t you feel sad for him?

624
00:51:00,000 --> 00:51:03,920
Just think about it, all that Jerry does is search for food

625
00:51:03,920 --> 00:51:06,240
And Tom always bullies him.

626
00:51:08,000 --> 00:51:12,080
I want to be like Tom and Jerry

627
00:51:12,280 --> 00:51:13,440
Why?

628
00:51:14,440 --> 00:51:19,400
Even though they always fight, they never leave each other.

629
00:51:20,080 --> 00:51:22,720
I’ll be Jerry and you’ll be Tom.

630
00:51:26,040 --> 00:51:28,680
I like spending time together like this.

631
00:51:28,920 --> 00:51:31,560
We hardly have time to spend with each other.

632
00:51:31,640 --> 00:51:33,000
You missed me a lot then?

633
00:51:33,120 --> 00:51:35,240
Of course I do. You don’t miss me?

634
00:51:35,240 --> 00:51:38,120
Did I say I don’t? Huh?

635
00:51:41,480 --> 00:51:42,120
All good?

636
00:51:42,920 --> 00:51:45,320
I’ll just go to the bathroom.

637
00:52:05,680 --> 00:52:06,600
Hello?

638
00:52:43,520 --> 00:52:48,680
Mm... I’ll come over. Hmm... okay buh-bye.

639
00:53:00,480 --> 00:53:01,800
Guys, I have to move.

640
00:53:01,880 --> 00:53:03,560
Where the heck are you going? Our gig is tomorrow!

641
00:53:03,560 --> 00:53:05,200
Who cares? We already know the song, won’t make mistakes.

642
00:53:05,200 --> 00:53:09,080
I’m in a hurry and it’s important, so I’ll leave. Goodnight!

643
00:53:10,280 --> 00:53:13,240
Ah! He killed my spirit.

644
00:53:13,720 --> 00:53:15,640
We’ll wrap it up for now?

645
00:53:15,640 --> 00:53:19,840
We’ll come to practice early tomorrow for the rehearsal, that okay Mk?

646
00:53:20,640 --> 00:53:22,960
Fine, let’s do that.

647
00:53:43,120 --> 00:53:44,760
Look at Lilac

648
00:53:45,080 --> 00:53:48,320
She’s singing so great tonight.

649
00:54:00,680 --> 00:54:03,400
Le, le, le, le, are we ready?

650
00:54:03,520 --> 00:54:06,840
Why do we look so gloomy? And where is Dave?

651
00:54:07,360 --> 00:54:08,680
He’s on his way, John.

652
00:54:08,680 --> 00:54:10,960
He is just on his way? What’s going on!?

653
00:54:11,200 --> 00:54:13,680
Uh… he’s stuck in traffic.

654
00:54:15,080 --> 00:54:18,120
There’s no traffic jam at this hour.

655
00:54:18,480 --> 00:54:26,640
Mm. I’ll cancel the gig if he doesn’t reach here within 20 minutes. Call him right now!

656
00:54:26,640 --> 00:54:28,240
Call him!

657
00:54:37,080 --> 00:54:38,880
He’s finally here.

658
00:54:39,160 --> 00:54:40,520
What took you so long?

659
00:54:40,640 --> 00:54:41,640
Guys.

660
00:54:42,480 --> 00:54:43,680
Are you drunk!?

661
00:54:43,680 --> 00:54:44,920
I’m here anyway!

662
00:54:44,920 --> 00:54:46,560
Sober up! We’re going to start.

663
00:54:46,560 --> 00:54:48,040
Always shouting at me whenever--

664
00:54:48,040 --> 00:54:49,560
I’m haven’t shouted at you enough! Look at yourself!

665
00:54:49,560 --> 00:54:51,840
Why do I have to look at myself? Look at yourself instead!

666
00:54:51,840 --> 00:54:52,280
I swear I’ll-

667
00:54:52,280 --> 00:54:54,800
They’ve called our name, let’s go first.

668
00:55:12,920 --> 00:55:19,200
Without time wasted on you

669
00:55:19,480 --> 00:55:27,720
I finally heal from all the pain

670
00:55:28,080 --> 00:55:35,040
I know you’ve always denied our love

671
00:55:35,040 --> 00:55:41,320
My foolish heart was scared of losing you

672
00:55:42,760 --> 00:55:47,400
And now it’s getting late, your time’s run out

673
00:55:47,400 --> 00:55:51,000
There’s no use in regretting

674
00:55:51,280 --> 00:55:57,840
You never held me close in your heart

675
00:55:58,120 --> 00:55:59,920
If I knew what-

676
00:56:01,760 --> 00:56:05,440
Continue playing the song, do it.

677
00:56:06,560 --> 00:56:08,920
Look at Dave!

678
00:56:09,480 --> 00:56:12,040
He looks so drunk.

679
00:56:17,240 --> 00:56:18,120
Dave!

680
00:56:19,520 --> 00:56:21,760
-
Dave! The fuck is going with you?

681
00:56:22,200 --> 00:56:23,600
It was a minor mistake. Sorry.

682
00:56:23,600 --> 00:56:25,600
You embarrassed us out there!

683
00:56:25,600 --> 00:56:27,680
I said I’m sorry…

684
00:56:27,680 --> 00:56:31,320
You’re sorry? How many times have I told you to fix yourself?

685
00:56:33,120 --> 00:56:37,200
As if you have never done anything wrong. Don’t think you’re at the top just because you’re the band leader.

686
00:56:37,200 --> 00:56:38,480
How dare you!

687
00:56:38,480 --> 00:56:39,560
Hey! Stop it!

688
00:56:39,560 --> 00:56:40,640
Let me go!

689
00:56:40,760 --> 00:56:41,640
Enough, enough.

690
00:56:42,360 --> 00:56:46,080
Let me tell you. You’re not going to find a better guitarist than me for this band.

691
00:56:46,080 --> 00:56:46,800
Hey! Hey!

692
00:56:46,800 --> 00:56:48,120
What the hell is wrong with you guys?

693
00:56:48,120 --> 00:56:50,560
Do you have no shame? There are so many people around!

694
00:56:50,560 --> 00:56:52,600
Making such a huge ruckus.
- Dave, Dave, Dave!

695
00:56:52,960 --> 00:56:56,760
Run after Dave. Go! Run after him now!

696
00:57:15,640 --> 00:57:18,760
You can’t get through to Dave?

697
00:57:25,280 --> 00:57:28,400
Look at this.

698
00:57:28,760 --> 00:57:32,240
You know that you have breached the contract right?

699
00:57:32,560 --> 00:57:34,920
We’re sorry, John.

700
00:57:39,680 --> 00:57:44,400
Saying sorry doesn’t fix anything.

701
00:57:45,720 --> 00:57:52,280
Think about it. You were going to be at the peak of your fame.

702
00:57:52,280 --> 00:57:56,200
-
Mistakes can cause dire consequences.

703
00:57:58,120 --> 00:58:02,800
We’re coming up with a new song, we’ll recover.

704
00:58:08,280 --> 00:58:10,360
You’ll have a new song?

705
00:58:12,600 --> 00:58:16,200
But what of Dave?

706
00:58:33,960 --> 00:58:35,840
What did John say?

707
00:58:42,480 --> 00:58:45,840
He made me sign a settlement agreement for the breach of contract.

708
00:58:48,440 --> 00:58:53,920
He gave us time to get everything sorted out but we can’t do it without Dave.

709
00:58:57,960 --> 00:58:59,600
Where’s Pete?

710
00:59:00,120 --> 00:59:03,120
His family called him so he left.

711
00:59:05,600 --> 00:59:06,800
You’re not gonna go home yet?

712
00:59:06,800 --> 00:59:08,520
Mm. I’ll stay for a while.

713
00:59:14,360 --> 00:59:16,680
Zo, does this mean we have disbanded?

714
00:59:20,640 --> 00:59:26,520
I’ve never mentioned this, but, I never had anything…

715
00:59:29,160 --> 00:59:33,360
the things I’ve said about my parents, they were all lies

716
00:59:36,920 --> 00:59:39,800
I never got a chance to see them…

717
00:59:43,000 --> 00:59:48,440
My uncle took care of me… I make up these lies to fit in.

718
00:59:51,880 --> 00:59:55,800
Then I get to have such great friends in college

59:58.000 --> 01:00:02.200
And now, you guys are not just friends, you’re my only family,

01:00:06.200 --> 01:00:09.240
I’m losing the only family that I have.

01:00:13.440 --> 01:00:17.000
You go ahead, I’ll stay for a while.

01:01:04.320 --> 01:01:05.360
How are you, Betsie?

01:01:05.360 --> 01:01:06.600
What do you want?

01:01:08.040 --> 01:01:11.040
Don’t you miss me at all? We haven’t spoken for ages.

01:01:11.120 --> 01:01:14.520
We have been separated for so long now, Zuala, why do you continue bothering me?

01:01:14.520 --> 01:01:20.520
We haven’t even signed our divorce papers yet. You’re still my wife by law.

01:01:20.520 --> 01:01:24.120
I’d rather choose death than be your wife.

01:01:24.880 --> 01:01:29.960
Do you think you’ll be able to honour vows when you can’t even honour ours?

01:01:30.200 --> 01:01:33.120
And you’re saying that you’re dating a celebrity.

01:01:33.720 --> 01:01:36.160
Do you know how others are talking behind your back?

01:01:36.160 --> 01:01:38.680
People are gossiping about the fact that we’re separated.

01:01:38.680 --> 01:01:43.560
I do not owe you anything. Being married to you was worse than hell.

01:01:43.560 --> 01:01:47.320
Zodina is a much better man than you’ll ever be.

01:01:47.320 --> 01:01:51.840
And you? You’re nothing. You’re nothing but a man who beats his wife up.

01:01:51.840 --> 01:01:55.360
Marrying you was the worst decision of my life.

01:01:55.360 --> 01:01:58.400
I’d rather stay a divorcee than bring you back into my life.

01:01:58.400 --> 01:01:59.080
Damn bitch.

01:01:59.080 --> 01:02:04.440
Slap me if you dare! Do you think I’m still scared of you? I’m not intimidated by you in the least.

01:02:04.440 --> 01:02:07.960
I’m not even your wife anymore, don’t ever show your face in front of me again.

01:02:15.440 --> 01:02:18.480
Feli, where is your sister?

01:02:18.480 --> 01:02:21.240
She’s upstairs. You can go upstairs.

01:02:35.440 --> 01:02:36.400
Zo…

01:02:36.400 --> 01:02:39.800
Where were you today? Why didn’t you answer my calls?

01:02:40.200 --> 01:02:42.320
I went to the bazaar.

01:02:47.960 --> 01:02:49.400
Who is this man?

01:02:49.400 --> 01:02:51.600
Zo, it’s not what you think-
Who is he?

01:02:51.600 --> 01:02:52.760
Who!?

01:02:52.760 --> 01:02:54.880
That’s Zuala, my ex-husband.

01:02:56.120 --> 01:02:59.680
Beth, you want to go back to your husband after all that we’ve been through?

01:03:00.240 --> 01:03:03.800
I’m telling you the truth, there is nothing between us.

01:03:04.040 --> 01:03:09.440
I want to believe you. I really want to believe you, but I can’t.

01:03:12.800 --> 01:03:15.240
Don’t say whatever you want based on assumptions.

01:03:15.240 --> 01:03:17.680
Then tell me what I don’t know!

01:03:17.680 --> 01:03:19.360
All those times we’ve spent together, were they lies?

01:03:19.440 --> 01:03:21.560
Stop talking, Zodinsang!

01:03:21.560 --> 01:03:24.400
There is nothing between me and Zuala.

01:03:24.400 --> 01:03:27.200
I faced him with  every strength I had only because of you.

01:03:27.200 --> 01:03:31.160
You should have told me that you met him. You should’ve told me!

01:03:31.160 --> 01:03:36.880
I’ve always wanted to tell you! There is nothing between me and him.

01:03:36.880 --> 01:03:42.480
I didn’t want my past to interfere with us, so I wanted to resolve things on my own… now I’ve resolved it, it’s done.

01:03:42.480 --> 01:03:43.760
Beth…

01:03:43.760 --> 01:03:46.800
Zo, please leave me alone for now.

01:04:08.160 --> 01:04:10.440
Sis, all good?

01:04:10.440 --> 01:04:14.000
Good. I’m going to my room, don’t disturb me.

01:05:49.920 --> 01:05:55.640
Zodin, what are you doing?
My sister’s in her room, go.

01:06:06.160 --> 01:06:14.760
The blue moon and the stars count the tears I’ve cried

01:06:14.760 --> 01:06:22.920
My tears will merge with the rain that has kissed the earth

01:06:22.920 --> 01:06:31.800
My sorrow stayed even as the sun went down

01:06:32.080 --> 01:06:39.440
And I’ll lie down without owning happiness

01:06:39.440 --> 01:06:47.720
Please, don’t give me hope

01:06:47.720 --> 01:06:55.720
Watch me as I fall from giving up…

01:06:55.720 --> 01:07:03.680
Don’t let your heart ache because of me

01:07:03.680 --> 01:07:10.920
Don’t let the voice of this hopeless person reach your ears,

01:07:10.920 --> 01:07:21.560
Lay me down so I can heal

01:07:52.400 --> 01:07:56.600
Let’s not keep any more secrets between us,

01:07:56.600 --> 01:08:01.120
be it our personal problems or whatever problems we may have…

01:08:01.120 --> 01:08:04.080
let’s face them together.

01:08:05.080 --> 01:08:10.640
Zo… I find this so hard to tell you…

01:08:12.040 --> 01:08:15.680
I told you, no more secrets.

01:08:26.000 --> 01:08:27.960
What is it that you’re hiding from me?

01:08:28.640 --> 01:08:30.080
I can’t tell you.

01:08:30.080 --> 01:08:31.640
Why can’t you?

01:08:34.120 --> 01:08:35.240
I can’t.

01:08:35.240 --> 01:08:36.480
Please tell me, Beth.

01:08:39.600 --> 01:08:40.720
Tell me.

01:08:47.280 --> 01:08:50.440
Zo, I don’t have much time to live.

01:08:50.800 --> 01:08:52.400
What are you saying?

01:08:52.400 --> 01:08:55.040
I have cancer.

01:08:56.840 --> 01:09:03.960
We received the news from my tests last week and its stage 4.

01:09:07.040 --> 01:09:12.640
Zo, please forgive me.

01:09:13.160 --> 01:09:17.320
I don’t want you to suffer because of my disease.

01:09:22.640 --> 01:09:27.600
But I can’t do it… I can’t take it anymore, I need you.

01:09:27.840 --> 01:09:33.240
I want you… I need you by my side…

01:10:41.440 --> 01:10:50.520
One by one, you take everyone I love away from me…

01:10:50.520 --> 01:10:55.760
Why Betsie?

01:10:56.640 --> 01:11:00.760
Why her?

01:11:03.360 --> 01:11:12.320
Please, God, don’t take her from me.

01:11:25.320 --> 01:11:29.000
You’re home, dear.

01:11:29.280 --> 01:11:31.200
I came home a while back.

01:11:31.200 --> 01:11:33.160
Why do you look so unhappy?

01:11:33.240 --> 01:11:34.400
It’s nothing, mom, I’m good.

01:11:34.480 --> 01:11:36.240
Come, sit with me, dear.

01:11:45.000 --> 01:11:50.360
I’m your mother and I know you well, so tell me, son.

01:11:57.120 --> 01:12:04.160
Mom… Betsie has cancer.

01:12:10.800 --> 01:12:12.880
I don’t know what I’m going to do.

01:12:13.360 --> 01:12:15.680
I’m so sorry.

01:12:18.960 --> 01:12:20.680
I’m helpless, mom.

01:12:21.040 --> 01:12:24.480
Don’t worry, dear, everything will be okay.

01:12:25.240 --> 01:12:28.080
Why does God give only to take it away?

01:12:28.080 --> 01:12:33.600
Never say that again. God’s plan is always directed towards what’s best for us.

01:12:33.600 --> 01:12:40.800
Nothing is meant to stay forever, everything has its time.

01:12:40.800 --> 01:12:47.240
Rather than grieving for what is lost, we should be grateful for the brief moment that we had it.

01:12:47.240 --> 01:12:54.440
Now go spend as much time as you can with Betsie, and don’t think about the rest, okay?

01:13:17.720 --> 01:13:18.680
Is anyone home?

01:13:18.680 --> 01:13:23.000
Oh? Come inside. Oi! This is a surprise.

01:13:23.000 --> 01:13:24.160
What are you doing?

01:13:24.160 --> 01:13:26.520
I was just cleaning the house.

01:13:27.160 --> 01:13:29.560
You didn’t you tell me beforehand…

01:13:30.680 --> 01:13:32.280
I want to show you something.

01:13:32.280 --> 01:13:33.640
What is it?

01:13:39.520 --> 01:13:40.440
We’re going to Europe?

01:13:40.440 --> 01:13:41.480
Yes!

01:13:45.200 --> 01:13:47.280
I promised you., didn’t I?

01:13:47.280 --> 01:13:49.440
Promise
- Promise

01:14:04.440 --> 01:14:11.120
Out of everybody, you’re the only one I want

01:14:11.120 --> 01:14:17.560
Oh, it been you and only you

01:14:17.720 --> 01:14:24.360
Let’s swear on our lives and promise to stay together

01:14:24.360 --> 01:14:30.920
I love staying in your arms

01:14:34.360 --> 01:14:37.920
If Pete and Mk were here, they’d chase each other by now.

01:14:38.680 --> 01:14:41.720
Pete would be in some sort of accident by now.

01:14:43.680 --> 01:14:46.520
And Dave? Did you guys talk?

01:14:46.520 --> 01:14:48.120
Mmm.

01:14:49.160 --> 01:14:59.200
Hmm, you need to be the bigger person in this situation. Talk to him when we go home, okay?
We vowed to never take back our promises

01:14:59.200 --> 01:15:00.520
I don’t know.

01:15:01.240 --> 01:15:02.560
It’ll all work out.

01:15:21.160 --> 01:15:27.920
Hold my hand tight, never let go

01:15:27.920 --> 01:15:34.560
We vowed to never take back our promises

01:15:34.560 --> 01:15:41.120
Even when we’re lain side by side to return to earth

01:15:41.120 --> 01:15:50.920
Together we’ll soar and find our place in the sky

01:16:36.760 --> 01:16:37.360
Beth…

01:16:37.640 --> 01:16:38.720
Mm?

01:16:39.040 --> 01:16:40.520
Can you give me your phone?

01:16:41.160 --> 01:16:44.720
Go stand over there, I’ll take your photo.

01:16:46.840 --> 01:16:50.200
Beth… will you marry me?

01:17:53.960 --> 01:17:58.680
Zodin… Are you sure you made the right decision?

01:18:01.480 --> 01:18:07.520
I don’t know how we’ll meet in the sky…

01:18:08.440 --> 01:18:11.560
so the time that we have now, I want to spend them with you.

01:18:14.320 --> 01:18:24.160
Yeah… they say that everyone, even our loved ones roam the sky… So it’s also ours.

01:18:24.800 --> 01:18:27.920
You won’t like heaven without me anyway.

01:18:28.000 --> 01:18:32.280
You’re not trying to make me live long, aren’t you?

01:19:28.960 --> 01:19:32.640
Hi, Zodin, I need to talk to Betsie’s family.

01:19:32.760 --> 01:19:33.960
It’s just me today.

01:19:33.960 --> 01:19:36.000
Can I talk to you regarding Betsie?

01:19:36.040 --> 01:19:36.640
Of course.

01:19:38.560 --> 01:19:45.680
We’re doing our best but we believe Betsie may not have much time left…

01:19:46.240 --> 01:19:53.760
The cancer has spread extensively and has caused significant damage. Her condition is unpredictable, so you have to prepare yourself for the worst.

01:19:54.640 --> 01:19:58.240
Make sure that she spend her remaining days filled with happiness.

01:20:58.880 --> 01:21:01.160
Where did you go?

01:21:01.200 --> 01:21:03.480
I went to the shop… how do you feel?

01:21:03.480 --> 01:21:05.040
I’m fine...

01:21:08.440 --> 01:21:09.360
Really?

01:21:09.560 --> 01:21:14.000
Mm. But I’m so tired of being in the hospital.

01:21:14.800 --> 01:21:16.440
Do you want ot get fresh air?

01:21:17.040 --> 01:21:18.200
Mm.

01:21:19.760 --> 01:21:23.120
Get enough rest first, and then we’ll go out.

01:21:25.240 --> 01:21:27.520
I want to climb a mountain.

01:21:28.320 --> 01:21:29.240
You want to climb a mountain?

01:21:29.240 --> 01:21:30.160
Mm.

01:21:31.160 --> 01:21:32.440
Which mountain do you want to go to?

01:21:33.320 --> 01:21:35.840
A really nice mountain.

01:21:44.200 --> 01:21:46.480
Take me there later, okay?

01:22:32.200 --> 01:22:35.960
Do you feel peaceful? scared?

01:22:37.440 --> 01:22:40.720
No, I’m not scared, but…

01:22:42.920 --> 01:22:49.720
When I have to leave, I don’t want to see you in pain…

01:23:02.120 --> 01:23:06.080
If our loved ones are hurt, the person who loves also gets hurt…

01:23:06.840 --> 01:23:07.440
Zo…

01:23:07.680 --> 01:23:09.440
Hmm?

01:23:12.480 --> 01:23:16.880
I want you to be happy even when I leave…

01:23:17.160 --> 01:23:26.160
besides, when our days on earth have drawn to a close, the sky is ours. I’ll wait for you.

01:24:33.600 --> 01:24:35.520
Are you in touch with Dave?

01:24:36.800 --> 01:24:40.800
He’s out of touch with everyone these days, wonder what’s wrong with him.

01:24:41.680 --> 01:24:46.880
Yes, Zodin? Yeah… what?

01:24:48.320 --> 01:24:50.160
Okay… all right.

01:24:51.120 --> 01:24:53.160
Betsie’s condition got worse, we need to leave now.

01:24:53.400 --> 01:24:57.600
Oh, really? Wait, let me just update Dave.

01:25:00.720 --> 01:25:02.400
Yeah, hello?

01:28:07.280 --> 01:28:08.200
Am I late?

01:28:08.200 --> 01:28:09.800
Not late at all. How are you?

01:28:09.800 --> 01:28:10.640
I’m good.

01:28:10.760 --> 01:28:14.960
My sister told me to give this to you before she passed away.

01:28:56.560 --> 01:28:58.160
Hello...

01:29:01.240 --> 01:29:06.320
If you’ve watching this video, it means I would’ve passed away.

01:29:09.040 --> 01:29:16.640
I wanted to make a short video before my disease eats me up...

01:29:18.680 --> 01:29:33.480
Zodin, I told you not to be lonely and miserable. Look at your face now... I told you I can’t stand you being lonely...

01:29:36.520 --> 01:29:58.880
but... whenever you miss me or want to talk to me or want to see my face...just look up at the sky... I’ll be up in the heavens that time... I’ll look over you from above...

01:29:59.560 --> 01:30:21.240
Don’t feel alone... you have your friends with you, I’ll be here if you ever want to talk... all you have to do is look up... this is so hard...

01:30:24.640 --> 01:30:43.880
Even the others... Dave, life is great isn’t it? Enjoy all you want but know that your friends love you so much...

01:30:44.040 --> 01:30:54.560
Don’t take all the burden to yourself... please remember that your friends are like your family, you can confide in them

01:30:54.760 --> 01:31:04.160
and I know how much you love them and need them... so... stick close to them...

01:31:05.960 --> 01:31:13.800
Mk... look at your friends, none of them are happy...

01:31:13.800 --> 01:31:19.600
and none of them will be happy without you, so keep on being the sunshine... it’s your responsibility now.

01:31:20.600 --> 01:31:25.240
never forget that your friends are your family...

01:31:25.240 --> 01:31:32.560
and finally, Pete, don’t think that I’ve missed you out, I didn’t forget you.

01:31:33.480 --> 01:31:44.840
I know you don’t talk a lot but never forget how precious you are to your friends...

01:31:45.640 --> 01:31:51.720
the four of you need each other so never turn your back on each other.

01:31:52.080 --> 01:32:14.200
Zodin, everything that I had been though... you made me forget my worst memories by spending time with you... I’m so grateful.. but I’m sorry...

01:32:16.440 --> 01:32:34.000
I wish I could stay with you forever... I wrote a song for you... and its in this pendrive... please listen to it and I hope you like it...

01:32:34.000 --> 01:32:56.040
and... Zodin... even though our time was short, you’ve made it my heaven on earth and thank you for leaving me with no regrets... thank you for loving me, and you know that I love you too...

01:33:06.520 --> 01:33:15.000
For tonight’s Thazual Award performance, we’ll call to the stage the youth sensation. They have been the chart toppers for quite a while

01:33:15.000 --> 01:33:27.080
and they have left their marks not just in Mizoram but abroad as well, let’s call out The Hangout Boys. They’re dedicating this song to Betsie who had passed away.
